      "id": "RQ-0004",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Harden webhook URL validation against unsafe destinations",
      "description": "Per the audit, `WebhookConfig.url` is passed to delivery without scheme allowlist or SSRF-style guards (loopback, link-local, IMDS-style hosts). Implement validation in `contracts/config/webhook.rs`: prefer HTTPS-only by default, optional opt-in for plaintext, and validation-time warnings or rejects for risky targets. Outcome: webhook destinations cannot trivially pivot to local/metadata endpoints without explicit operator intent.\n\nValidation: `WebhookConfig` in `crates/ralph/src/contracts/config/webhook.rs` exposes `url: Option<String>` (serde field) with merge/event/timeout fields documented, but there is no URL safety policy in that module today; `deliver_attempt` in `webhook/worker/delivery.rs` forwards the configured URL string straight into `send_request`.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "audit",
        "security",
        "webhook",
        "config"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/contracts/config/webhook.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/delivery.rs",
        "schemas/",
        "cargo test -p ralph"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "User requested tasks from `/tmp/ralph-codebase-audit.md` (Finding #2, Security section on `WebhookConfig.url`, Quick win #2).",
        "Repo: `crates/ralph/src/contracts/config/webhook.rs` (`WebhookConfig.url`); delivery uses `msg.config.url` in `deliver_attempt`; `queue validate` passed (2026-04-16)."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Trace config load/merge path for `WebhookConfig` and where URL is first considered valid.",
        "Review `/tmp/ralph-codebase-audit.md` security subsection and Quick win #2 if available.",
        "Design allowlist/default-HTTPS policy and config knob if needed (align with schema + docs patterns).",
        "Implement URL validation with tests covering loopback, link-local, and acceptable HTTPS cases.",
        "Run `cargo test -p ralph` for affected modules."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "Validate `WebhookConfig.url` usage end-to-end (`contracts/config/webhook.rs` through `webhook/worker/delivery.rs`). Add URL safety: default HTTPS-only, optional opt-in for http, and reject or clearly warn on loopback, link-local, and metadata-style hosts unless explicitly allowed. Update schema/tests as needed. Run `cargo test -p ralph`. Scope: this task only‚Äîno new queue items.",
