      "id": "RQ-0006",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Implement exponential webhook retry backoff with jitter and cap",
      "description": "Audit notes `webhook/worker/delivery.rs::retry_delay` uses linear backoff (`base √ó retry_number`), which can hammer endpoints during outages. Switch to exponential backoff with jitter and a maximum cap, preserving existing timeout/redaction behavior. Outcome: retry storm risk is reduced under prolonged failures.\n\nValidation: `retry_delay` is `Duration::from_millis(base.as_millis().saturating_mul(retry_number as u128).min(...))` ‚Äî strictly linear in `retry_number` with no jitter or exponential term.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "audit",
        "webhook",
        "performance",
        "resilience"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/delivery.rs",
        "cargo test -p ralph"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "User requested tasks from `/tmp/ralph-codebase-audit.md` (Finding #5, Performance section on `retry_delay`, Quick win #4).",
        "Repo: `crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/delivery.rs` `fn retry_delay(base: Duration, retry_number: u32)` (~lines 112‚Äì117); `queue validate` passed (2026-04-16)."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Inspect current `retry_delay` and call graph in `delivery.rs` (scheduled retry path uses `retry_delay(task.msg.config.retry_backoff, retry_number)`).",
        "Implement exponential+jitter+cap with deterministic unit tests for backoff sequence bounds.",
        "Validate behavior under configured retry limits and document any config surface changes if required.",
        "Run webhook delivery tests."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "Replace linear `retry_delay` in `crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/delivery.rs` with exponential backoff, jitter, and a maximum cap; keep existing timeout and redaction behavior. Add tests for bounded delay sequences. Run webhook delivery tests. Scope: this task only‚Äîno new queue items.",
