    {
      "id": "RQ-0005",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Replace webhook runtime thread-spawn `.expect()` with graceful degradation",
      "description": "`webhook/worker/runtime.rs` uses `.expect()` when spawning delivery workers; under resource pressure this can abort the whole CLI. Return `Result` (or equivalent) and degrade to synchronous delivery or disable webhooks for the run with a clear operator-visible warning. Outcome: webhook subsystem does not crash the process on thread spawn failure.\n\nValidation: `WebhookDispatcher::new` in `crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/runtime.rs` panics on `startup_sender.send`, `thread::Builder::spawn`, startup `recv_timeout`, and `dispatcher_for_config` uses `.expect(\"dispatcher initialized\")` on the cached dispatcher.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "audit",
        "webhook",
        "resilience",
        "error-handling"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/runtime.rs",
        "cargo test -p ralph"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "User requested tasks from `/tmp/ralph-codebase-audit.md` (Finding #4, Error Handling section with `runtime.rs` cite, Quick win #3).",
        "Repo: `crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/runtime.rs` lines ~164‚Äì188 (`expect` on worker/scheduler spawn and startup handshake), ~236 (`expect(\"dispatcher initialized\")`); `queue validate` passed (2026-04-16)."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Inventory all `.expect(` sites in `webhook/worker/runtime.rs` (worker spawn, scheduler spawn, startup barrier, dispatcher cache).",
        "Read audit Quick win #3 if available.",
        "Refactor spawn paths to propagate errors and choose a documented fallback path.",
        "Add regression tests simulating failure where feasible (or unit-test the decision helper).",
        "Run targeted webhook/runtime tests."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "In `crates/ralph/src/webhook/worker/runtime.rs`, replace `.expect()` on worker/scheduler spawn, startup handshake, and dispatcher init with `Result` propagation and a defined fallback: degrade to sync delivery or disable webhooks for the run with a clear operator-visible warning‚Äîno process abort on thread spawn failure. Add regression coverage where practical. Run webhook/runtime tests. Scope: this task only‚Äîno new queue items.",
