    {
      "id": "RQ-0008",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Make runner stream decoding UTF-8 safe across fixed read chunks",
      "description": "`runner/execution/stream_reader.rs` uses `String::from_utf8_lossy` on fixed 8KB chunks, which can split UTF-8 sequences and emit replacement characters. Buffer partial UTF-8 across reads or use a line-oriented decode strategy appropriate for the stream format. Outcome: non-ASCII runner output renders correctly without U+FFFD artifacts from chunk boundaries.\n\nValidation: Both `spawn_reader` and `spawn_json_reader` use `let mut buf = [0u8; 8192]` then `String::from_utf8_lossy(&buf[..read])` before line assembly / `append_to_buffer`, so multibyte sequences split across reads can surface as U+FFFD in the lossy string path.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "audit",
        "correctness",
        "runner",
        "streaming"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/runner/execution/stream_reader.rs",
        "cargo test -p ralph"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "User requested tasks from `/tmp/ralph-codebase-audit.md` (Finding #3, Rust-specific section, Short-term #6).",
        "Repo: `crates/ralph/src/runner/execution/stream_reader.rs` (`spawn_reader` ~35‚Äì42, `spawn_json_reader` ~68‚Äì80); `queue validate` passed (2026-04-16)."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Re-read audit Finding #3 and proposed fixes if available.",
        "Implement cross-chunk UTF-8 buffering (or alternative) with focused unit tests including split codepoints.",
        "Regression-test representative runner stream parsing paths if present."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "Fix UTF-8 safety in `crates/ralph/src/runner/execution/stream_reader.rs`: avoid `from_utf8_lossy` on raw 8KB chunks splitting multibyte sequences; buffer partial UTF-8 across reads or decode in a line-safe way so runner NDJSON/text does not show U+FFFD at chunk boundaries. Add tests with split codepoints. Run `cargo test -p ralph` for stream reader paths. Scope: this task only‚Äîno new queue items.",
